  ('EX160','Seated Paddling Position Endurance','Isometric','Canoeing','Kneeling position in whitewater canoe is distinct from seated kayak; hip flexors, knees, and ankles all load differently','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX162','Tandem Canoe Coordination Drill','Technical / Skill','Canoeing','Canoe is inherently a tandem boat in AR; coordination failure costs more than fitness gaps — this is the primary efficiency lever','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX163','Canoe Portage Yoke Carry','Technical / Skill','Canoeing','The standard canoe portage method; technique determines whether a portage is manageable or a race-ending ordeal','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX166','Ferry & Eddy Turn Technique','Technical / Skill','Canoeing','Whitewater navigation fundamentals; open canoes require earlier and more committed ferry angles than kayaks','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX090','Paddling Ergometer Session','Aerobic / Endurance','Canoeing','Aerobic base and stroke conditioning; switch to single-blade paddle on erg if available to match canoe mechanics','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX091','Forward Stroke Technique Drill','Technical / Skill','Canoeing','Single-blade forward stroke; catch near feet, torso unwinds, exit at hip — same principle as kayak but one side at a time','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX087','Cable High-to-Low Chop','Strength','Canoeing','Most directly mimics the single-blade forward stroke plane; higher priority here than in kayaking because single-blade demands more pure pull per stroke','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX088','Russian Twist (DB / Med Ball)','Strength','Canoeing','Rotational core endurance; single-blade canoeing demands more sustained unilateral rotation than double-blade — this becomes Critical at race pace over hours','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX086','Landmine Rotation','Power','Canoeing','Single-blade rotational power; each stroke is a unilateral hip-driven rotation — power on one side is the limiting factor','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX085','Med Ball Rotational Throw (Wall)','Power','Canoeing','Explosive unilateral rotation; builds the power phase of the single-blade stroke','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX078','Single-Arm DB Row','Strength','Canoeing','Single-arm pull directly mirrors the single-blade stroke; higher carryover here than in kayak','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX079','Seated Cable Row (Narrow Grip)','Strength','Canoeing','Bilateral pulling base; also trains the symmetry that prevents stroke-side shoulder overuse','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX080','Lat Pulldown (Wide Grip)','Strength','Canoeing','Lat strength for the pull phase; single-blade requires more lat endurance per stroke than double-blade','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX006','Pull-Up (BW)','Strength','Canoeing','Upper back strength base for sustained single-blade pulling','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX016','Thoracic Rotation Drill','Mobility','Canoeing','Most important mobility drill for canoeing; single-blade demands more T-spine range than any other paddle discipline','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX089','Hollow Body Hold','Isometric','Canoeing','Core tension for power transfer; an open canoe requires constant postural control in all water conditions','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX011','Pallof Press (Band/Cable)','Isometric','Canoeing','Anti-rotation stability; the asymmetric pull of single-blade paddling creates a persistent rotation demand on the core','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX082','External Rotation (Band / Cable)','Activation / Primer','Canoeing','Rotator cuff prehab; single-blade asymmetry overloads the stroke-side shoulder more than double-blade','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX081','Band Face Pull','Activation / Primer','Canoeing','Rear delt and external rotator activation; pre-session prehab for stroke-side shoulder','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX083','Serratus Punch','Activation / Primer','Canoeing','Scapular stability; scapular winging on the stroke side is a common canoe overuse pattern','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX096','90/90 Shoulder Stretch','Flexibility / Stretching','Canoeing','Anterior shoulder; single-blade paddling loads the stroke-side shoulder into internal rotation over time','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX095','Portage Carry Simulation','Loaded Carry','Canoeing','General portage conditioning; canoe portage sections in AR are often longer than packraft portages','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX009','Farmer Carry','Loaded Carry','Canoeing','Grip, trap, and core endurance for gear portage alongside the boat','Medium','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX158','Whitewater Line Reading','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','The guide''s primary responsibility; a raft has far less manoeuvrability than a kayak — line selection must account for the boat''s momentum and width','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX164','High-Side Command Response Drill','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Safety-critical; failure to high-side on command is the primary cause of raft wraps and gear loss; must be reflexive for the whole team','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX165','Raft Paddle Synchronisation & Power Phase','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Team synchronisation is the dominant performance variable in rafting; synchronised moderate effort beats unsynchronised high effort','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX160','Seated Paddling Position Endurance','Isometric','Paddle Rafting','Raft tube seating is unstable; maintaining position on a bouncing tube for hours requires specific postural endurance distinct from flat-seat paddling','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX157','Draw Stroke & Pry Technique','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Lateral raft control for guide and bow paddler; draws and pries position the raft for difficult lines when forward strokes alone are insufficient','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX156','Sweep Stroke Technique Drill','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Turning the raft; sweep strokes from bow (turns bow away) and stern (pivot turn) are the primary raft steering tools','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX085','Med Ball Rotational Throw (Wall)','Power','Paddle Rafting','Explosive short-duration power for the raft power stroke; raft paddling is more anaerobic per stroke than kayaking','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX087','Cable High-to-Low Chop','Strength','Paddle Rafting','Simulates the power stroke plane; high-tempo team paddling demands rotational pulling strength','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX078','Single-Arm DB Row','Strength','Paddle Rafting','Unilateral pulling for the power stroke; each team member contributes single-side power per stroke','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX089','Hollow Body Hold','Isometric','Paddle Rafting','Core stability on an unstable bouncing platform; a soft core wastes power and makes high-side slower','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX082','External Rotation (Band / Cable)','Activation / Primer','Paddle Rafting','Rotator cuff prehab; high-side positions and bracing in rapids load the shoulder into vulnerable positions','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX081','Band Face Pull','Activation / Primer','Paddle Rafting','Rear delt activation; pre-session shoulder health before high-tempo team paddling','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX016','Thoracic Rotation Drill','Mobility','Paddle Rafting','T-spine rotation for full power stroke; restricted T-spine limits team paddling power even when arms are strong','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX011','Pallof Press (Band/Cable)','Isometric','Paddle Rafting','Core anti-rotation for stability on the unstable raft tube; resist the rocking motion to maintain stroke power','Medium','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX043','Single-Leg Balance Hold','Balance / Proprioception','Paddle Rafting','Balance on the raft tube; high-side and repositioning requires single-leg balance on a moving inflated surface','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX095','Portage Carry Simulation','Loaded Carry','Paddle Rafting','Inflatable raft portage; large rafts must be deflated and carried around unrunnable sections in AR','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX009','Farmer Carry','Loaded Carry','Paddle Rafting','Gear portage with raft; folded raft plus paddles plus gear is a substantial loaded carry','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX092','Bracing Stroke Drill (High and Low)','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Brace mechanics for guide and bow paddler; poor brace technique in rapids causes shoulder injury and reduces raft stability','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX166','Ferry & Eddy Turn Technique','Technical / Skill','Paddle Rafting','Raft ferrying in moving water; a large raft requires team coordination and early commitment to upstream ferry angle — the technique is the same but the execution window is much shorter due to mass','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX168','Skinning Uphill Technique','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','The primary SkiMo locomotion skill; skinning efficiency determines ascent pace on 80–90% of course distance','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX169','Ski Kick-Turn on Slope','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Direction reversal on steep skin tracks; a slow or failed kick-turn on steep terrain is a common time loss and fall risk','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX170','SkiMo Race Transition Drill','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Races are frequently decided in transitions; skin removal and crampon attachment under fatigue and cold must be automatic','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX171','Touring Ski Descent Technique','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Descent is the fastest and highest injury-risk phase; touring skis behave differently from resort skis and require specific technique','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX172','Lateral Ski Edge Control Drill','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Edge security on traverses and variable snow surfaces; glute med and ankle evertor weakness is the most common cause of lateral instability','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX173','Tuck Position Isometric Hold','Isometric','SkiMo','Descent tuck is held for extended minutes under accumulated fatigue; quad endurance in this specific position is a direct race limiter','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX148','Crampon Walking Technique','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','SkiMo courses include boot sections on steep ice and hard snow; crampon technique used identically to mountaineering legs','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX149','Ice Axe Self-Arrest','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Safety-critical on steep boot sections above ski depot; self-arrest must be automatic before entering consequential terrain','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX150','Rest Step Technique','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Pace management on long boot sections; rest step preserves legs for ski sections that follow','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX152','Post-Hole Recovery Gait','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Soft-snow boot sections between ski segments; energy management in unconsolidated snow is the same problem as mountaineering','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX048','Hill Repeats','Interval / Tempo','SkiMo','Uphill aerobic capacity is the primary SkiMo performance variable; steeper and longer repeats than trail running','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX073','Threshold Intervals (Bike)','Interval / Tempo','SkiMo','Best non-ski substitute for SkiMo aerobic training; cycling trainer preserves legs while building the aerobic base','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX075','Sweet Spot Training (Bike)','Interval / Tempo','SkiMo','Sustained aerobic output for long ascents; sweet spot builds the base that SkiMo demands on 1000m+ climbs','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX010','Rucking (Weighted Hike)','Loaded Carry','SkiMo','Off-snow substitute for skinning; pack-loaded uphill walking builds the specific aerobic and structural demand of skinning','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX050','Treadmill Incline Walk (Loaded Pack)','Loaded Carry','SkiMo','Hotel and indoor substitute for skinning; 12–15% grade with pack at sustained pace matches skinning aerobic demand','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX120','Sustained LISS (Hiking Pace)','Aerobic / Endurance','SkiMo','Time-on-feet under load for building the aerobic base and structural tolerance for multi-hour SkiMo efforts','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX001','Back Squat (Barbell)','Strength','SkiMo','Lower body strength base; descent quad load in touring skis under a pack is the primary structural demand','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX021','Bulgarian Split Squat (DB)','Strength','SkiMo','Single-leg eccentric control for touring ski descent; lateral instability is the failure mode — unilateral training addresses it','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX023','Lateral Lunge (DB or BW)','Strength','SkiMo','Hip abductor and adductor strength for lateral edging; sidehill traverse on skis demands the same lateral hip control as lateral lunges','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX012','Copenhagen Plank','Isometric','SkiMo','Adductor strength for ski edging and lateral stability; hip adductors are active in every carved turn and traverse','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX019','Barbell Hip Thrust','Strength','SkiMo','Glute max strength for uphill ski push-off and descent control; glutes are the primary stabiliser in the touring descent position','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX020','Nordic Hamstring Curl','Strength','SkiMo','Eccentric hamstring load for descent control; hamstring contribution to knee stability under eccentric ski load is well-established','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX037','Wall Sit','Isometric','SkiMo','VMO endurance in sustained flexion; wall sit at 100° hip angle mimics the tuck position demand','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX025','Single-Leg Calf Raise (Loaded)','Strength','SkiMo','Calf endurance for skinning push-off and boot-section crampon technique; calf is loaded constantly in walk-mode binding','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX030','Reverse Sled Drag','Strength','SkiMo','Eccentric VMO loading for descent braking; the quad-dominant descent demand of touring skiing is identical to the downhill braking load','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX017','Lateral Band Walk','Activation / Primer','SkiMo','Glute med pre-activation; glute med controls knee valgus in every ski turn and traverse — most common SkiMo alignment failure','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX040','Clamshell (Band)','Activation / Primer','SkiMo','Glute med activation; first step in pre-ski hip activation sequence','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX041','Monster Walk (Band)','Activation / Primer','SkiMo','Dynamic glute med activation; lateral locomotion pattern primes edging stabilisers','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX043','Single-Leg Balance Hold','Balance / Proprioception','SkiMo','Ankle and hip proprioception; ski boots reduce ankle mobility — hip stabiliser demand increases to compensate','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX044','BOSU Single-Leg Squat','Balance / Proprioception','SkiMo','Reactive balance on unstable surface; mimics the variable snow surface demand of SkiMo descent on variable crust','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX014','World''s Greatest Stretch','Mobility','SkiMo','Full lower chain mobility; hip flexors and T-spine are the biggest limiters in the sustained forward ski position','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX046','Hip Flexor Lunge Stretch','Flexibility / Stretching','SkiMo','Hip flexor recovery after sustained skinning; walk-mode binding keeps hip in constant flexion','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX076','Couch Stretch (Cyclist Hip Flexor)','Flexibility / Stretching','SkiMo','Deep hip flexor stretch; SkiMo forward lean in ski mode chronically shortens iliopsoas — do daily around ski days','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX015','Pigeon Pose','Flexibility / Stretching','SkiMo','Hip external rotator recovery; sustained edging and lateral hip demand tightens piriformis','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX047','Calf / Achilles Wall Stretch','Flexibility / Stretching','SkiMo','Calf recovery after skinning; Achilles is loaded heavily in walk mode and crampon boot sections','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX018','Foam Roll (IT Band / Quads / Lats)','Recovery / Soft Tissue','SkiMo','Post-descent quad and IT band recovery; eccentric ski load is similar to trail running downhill but sustained longer','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX124','Power Hiking Technique','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Active pole use transfers directly to skinning; pole push timing and mechanics are essentially identical','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX123','Pack Fit Optimization Drill','Technical / Skill','SkiMo','Pack fit matters more in SkiMo than most sports; a shifting pack changes ski balance — hip belt must be snug but allow leg drive','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX174','Aero / TT Position Hold','Isometric','Triathlon','The defining physical demand of triathlon cycling; aero position must be trained progressively or it becomes an injury source on race day','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX175','Brick Run Drill (Bike-to-Run Transition)','Technical / Skill','Triathlon','The most important triathlon-specific workout; bike-to-run adaptation cannot be trained by doing each discipline separately','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX176','Triathlon Transition Practice (T1 & T2)','Technical / Skill','Triathlon','Transitions are free speed; a 30-second T1 and T2 improvement requires zero fitness gain — only practice','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX126','Freestyle Pull (With Buoy)','Aerobic / Endurance','Triathlon','Primary swim strength and technique drill; isolates upper body pulling mechanics that drive triathlon swim pace','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX127','Band Swimming Shoulder Prehab (Y-T-W-L)','Activation / Primer','Triathlon','Shoulder injury prevention; swim volume in triathlon training is the primary shoulder overuse driver','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX128','Kicking Drill (Flutter / Frog)','Aerobic / Endurance','Triathlon','Kick efficiency; in triathlon the kick is deliberately suppressed to preserve legs for the bike — kick conditioning builds the capacity to choose how much to use it','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX129','Swim-Specific Rotational Core (Dry Land)','Strength','Triathlon','Body roll conditioning; rotation drives the catch and reduces shoulder stress in high-volume triathlon swim training','High','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('EX140','Open Water Sighting Drill','Technical / Skill','Triathlon','Navigation in open water without lane lines; sighting adds 3–8% to swim distance if done poorly — at triathlon distances that is minutes','Critical','0B-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
