  ('Aquathlon',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory',6.0,9.0,4.0,7.0,3.0,5.0,2.0,3.0,'SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1. FOCUS: Running-specific hip stability (aquathlon is run-dominant — glute med, single-leg work). Rotator cuff antagonists (swim volume demands shoulder antagonist balance). Core. No cycling load to manage, so strength can be placed more freely in the week.','included','SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','FOCUS: Running-specific hip stability (aquathlon is run-dominant — glute med, single-leg work). | Rotator cuff antagonists (swim volume demands shoulder antagonist balance). | Core. | No cycling load to manage, so strength can be placed more freely in the week.','SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1. FOCUS: Running-specific hip stability (aquathlon is run-dominant — glute med, single-leg work). Rotator cuff antagonists (swim volume demands shoulder antagonist balance). Core. No cycling load to manage, so strength can be placed more freely in the week.','strength','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Aquathlon',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,5.0,8.0,'% rises in Taper. CRITICAL: Shoulders (swim volume — posterior capsule stretch post every session). Hip flexors and calves (run-dominant event — standard running recovery). Cold water transition: if training open water, change out of wet clothing immediately post-session and monitor for hypothermia (especially relevant for northern/cold-water events).','included','% rises in Taper.','CRITICAL: Shoulders (swim volume — posterior capsule stretch post every session). | Hip flexors and calves (run-dominant event — standard running recovery). | Cold water transition: if training open water, change out of wet clothing immediately post-session and monitor for hypothermia (especially relevant for northern/cold-water events).','% rises in Taper. CRITICAL: Shoulders (swim volume — posterior capsule stretch post every session). Hip flexors and calves (run-dominant event — standard running recovery). Cold water transition: if training open water, change out of wet clothing immediately post-session and monitor for hypothermia (especially relevant for northern/cold-water events).','mobility','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
