  ('Aquabike',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory',6.0,8.0,4.0,6.0,3.0,5.0,2.0,3.0,'SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1. Higher cycling allocation means less strength recovery window — keep sessions short (30–45 min). FOCUS: Rotator cuff antagonists (high cycling volume does not protect shoulder — swim volume demands antagonist work). Core anti-extension (long aero position). Hip flexor and single-leg strength. No brick runs to manage, so slightly more flexibility in strength timing vs. triathlon.','included','SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','Higher cycling allocation means less strength recovery window — keep sessions short (30–45 min). | FOCUS: Rotator cuff antagonists (high cycling volume does not protect shoulder — swim volume demands antagonist work). | Core anti-extension (long aero position). | Hip flexor and single-leg strength. | No brick runs to manage, so slightly more flexibility in strength timing vs. | triathlon.','SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1. Higher cycling allocation means less strength recovery window — keep sessions short (30–45 min). FOCUS: Rotator cuff antagonists (high cycling volume does not protect shoulder — swim volume demands antagonist work). Core anti-extension (long aero position). Hip flexor and single-leg strength. No brick runs to manage, so slightly more flexibility in strength timing vs. triathlon.','strength','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Aquabike',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,5.0,8.0,'% rises in Taper. CRITICAL: Hip flexors (daily — no run after bike but 180km on bike still severely tightens hip flexors). Neck and thoracic (aggressive aero position — Aquabike athletes can use more aggressive aero fit than triathletes since no run-off hip angle constraint, but neck load is greater). Hamstrings. Post-long-ride: leg elevation 10–15 min before any other modality.','included','% rises in Taper.','CRITICAL: Hip flexors (daily — no run after bike but 180km on bike still severely tightens hip flexors). | Neck and thoracic (aggressive aero position — Aquabike athletes can use more aggressive aero fit than triathletes since no run-off hip angle constraint, but neck load is greater). | Hamstrings. | Post-long-ride: leg elevation 10–15 min before any other modality.','% rises in Taper. CRITICAL: Hip flexors (daily — no run after bike but 180km on bike still severely tightens hip flexors). Neck and thoracic (aggressive aero position — Aquabike athletes can use more aggressive aero fit than triathletes since no run-off hip angle constraint, but neck load is greater). Hamstrings. Post-long-ride: leg elevation 10–15 min before any other modality.','mobility','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
