  ('Mountain Running / Skyrunning',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory - Eccentric Priority',12.0,15.0,8.0,12.0,6.0,10.0,3.0,5.0,'ECCENTRIC EMPHASIS higher than standard trail running. Base: Bulgarian split squats, single-leg RDL, eccentric step-downs (3-5s lowering) - 3x/week. Build: Maintain 2x/week; add plyometrics for terrain reactivity. Peak: 1-2x/week maintenance focused on eccentric control.  CORE: Anti-rotation and extension for steep terrain stability.  [AUDIT 2026-05-05] Q-MF1: Family-leader Strength % (12-15% Base) is justified by PMC11586947 (Vertical Kilometer physiology study) finding maximum strength is the #2 performance predictor in BOTH uphill and downhill running, after maximal aerobic speed. Strength is a PRIMARY performance lever for skyrunning, not just injury prevention. Allocation supports 3x weekly sessions of 25-30 min in Base.','included','ECCENTRIC EMPHASIS higher than standard trail running.','Base: Bulgarian split squats, single-leg RDL, eccentric step-downs (3-5s lowering) - 3x/week. | Build: Maintain 2x/week; | add plyometrics for terrain reactivity. | Peak: 1-2x/week maintenance focused on eccentric control. | CORE: Anti-rotation and extension for steep terrain stability. | [AUDIT 2026-05-05] Q-MF1: Family-leader Strength % (12-15% Base) is justified by PMC11586947 (Vertical Kilometer physiology study) finding maximum strength is the #2 performance predictor in BOTH uphill and downhill running, after maximal aerobic speed. | Strength is a PRIMARY performance lever for skyrunning, not just injury prevention. | Allocation supports 3x weekly sessions of 25-30 min in Base.','ECCENTRIC EMPHASIS higher than standard trail running.
