  ('Mountain Running / Skyrunning',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',5.0,8.0,4.0,6.0,3.0,5.0,6.0,10.0,'Hip flexor and calf/Achilles priority (uphill). Quad and IT band priority (downhill EIMD). CWI after every steep downhill session - strongest CWI evidence is for eccentric EIMD.  [AUDIT 2026-05-05] PHASE SHAPE: % DROPS across Build/Peak (5-8 -> 4-6 -> 3-5) rather than holding flat or rising. Intentional. Build/Peak terrain-specific running displaces flexibility/range work; acute eccentric DOMS recovery handled via CWI rather than mobility time. Absolute time stays roughly constant 30-45 min/wk across all phases. Taper rebound to 6-10% is the explicit recovery phase.','included','Hip flexor and calf/Achilles priority (uphill).','Quad and IT band priority (downhill EIMD). | CWI after every steep downhill session - strongest CWI evidence is for eccentric EIMD. | [AUDIT 2026-05-05] PHASE SHAPE: % DROPS across Build/Peak (5-8 -> 4-6 -> 3-5) rather than holding flat or rising. | Intentional. | Build/Peak terrain-specific running displaces flexibility/range work; | acute eccentric DOMS recovery handled via CWI rather than mobility time. | Absolute time stays roughly constant 30-45 min/wk across all phases. | Taper rebound to 6-10% is the explicit recovery phase.','Hip flexor and calf/Achilles priority (uphill). Quad and IT band priority (downhill EIMD). CWI after every steep downhill session - strongest CWI evidence is for eccentric EIMD.

