  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Time Trial)',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory',5.0,12.0,6.0,8.0,4.0,6.0,2.0,3.0,'AERO EMPHASIS: Anterior core (anti-extension) is the primary strength demand — aero position requires sustained anterior core engagement to maintain flat back. Hip flexor and single-leg power (same as road). Glute activation. Neck strengthening (supported head position in aero — most reported TT complaint). SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','included','AERO EMPHASIS: Anterior core (anti-extension) is the primary strength demand — aero position requires sustained anterior','Hip flexor and single-leg power (same as road). | Glute activation. | Neck strengthening (supported head position in aero — most reported TT complaint). | SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','AERO EMPHASIS: Anterior core (anti-extension) is the primary strength demand — aero position requires sustained anterior core engagement to maintain flat back. Hip flexor and single-leg power (same as road). Glute activation. Neck strengthening (supported head position in aero — most reported TT complaint). SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','strength','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Time Trial)',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,2.0,5.0,5.0,8.0,'ADDITIONAL vs. road: Neck stretches post every aero session (flexion, extension, lateral rotation — 30s each). Thoracic extension over foam roller (counteracts sustained aero flexion). Hip flexor especially critical — aero position compresses hip angle more than road bike position. No position changes within 4 weeks of race.','included','ADDITIONAL vs.','road: Neck stretches post every aero session (flexion, extension, lateral rotation — 30s each). | Thoracic extension over foam roller (counteracts sustained aero flexion). | Hip flexor especially critical — aero position compresses hip angle more than road bike position. | No position changes within 4 weeks of race.','ADDITIONAL vs. road: Neck stretches post every aero session (flexion, extension, lateral rotation — 30s each). Thoracic extension over foam roller (counteracts sustained aero flexion). Hip flexor especially critical — aero position compresses hip angle more than road bike position. No position changes within 4 weeks of race.','mobility','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Time Trial)',NULL,'WEEKLY TOTAL TARGET','-',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 6–10 hrs | BUILD: 8–12 hrs | PEAK: 8–12 hrs | TAPER: 4–6 hrs  TT training is intensity-focused. Fewer hours than road/gravel but higher quality demands. AERO ADAPTATION PROTOCOL: Week 1–2: 20–30 min aero per session. Week 3–4: 45–60 min. Week 5–6: full ride in aero at easy pace. Week 7–8: intervals and quality work in aero. NEVER start race-duration aero without this progression — neck/lower back injury very likely.','included','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 6–10 hrs | BUILD: 8–12 hrs | PEAK: 8–12 hrs | TAPER: 4–6 hrs','TT training is intensity-focused. | Fewer hours than road/gravel but higher quality demands. | AERO ADAPTATION PROTOCOL: Week 1–2: 20–30 min aero per session. | Week 3–4: 45–60 min. | Week 5–6: full ride in aero at easy pace. | Week 7–8: intervals and quality work in aero. | NEVER start race-duration aero without this progression — neck/lower back injury very likely.','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 6–10 hrs | BUILD: 8–12 hrs | PEAK: 8–12 hrs | TAPER: 4–6 hrs

TT training is intensity-focused. Fewer hours than road/gravel but higher quality demands. AERO ADAPTATION PROTOCOL: Week 1–2: 20–30 min aero per session. Week 3–4: 45–60 min. Week 5–6: full ride in aero at easy pace. Week 7–8: intervals and quality work in aero. NEVER start race-duration aero without this progression — neck/lower back injury very likely.','weekly_total','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (XC Mountain Biking)','D-006','Road Cycling','Primary',47.0,52.0,42.0,50.0,38.0,48.0,50.0,60.0,'ROAD BASE IS MANDATORY: Build aerobic base on road/trainer before technical trail. 80/20 intensity applies. XCM (marathon) requires higher road base + long mixed rides (4–6 hrs). BASE = road foundation; Build/Peak = progressive trail introduction; Taper = back to road for aerobic freshness. Do not exceed 150% of prior longest trail session when introducing MTB.','included','ROAD BASE IS MANDATORY: Build aerobic base on road/trainer before technical trail.','80/20 intensity applies. | XCM (marathon) requires higher road base + long mixed rides (4–6 hrs). | BASE = road foundation; | Build/Peak = progressive trail introduction; | Taper = back to road for aerobic freshness. | Do not exceed 150% of prior longest trail session when introducing MTB.','ROAD BASE IS MANDATORY: Build aerobic base on road/trainer before technical trail. 80/20 intensity applies. XCM (marathon) requires higher road base + long mixed rides (4–6 hrs). BASE = road foundation; Build/Peak = progressive trail introduction; Taper = back to road for aerobic freshness. Do not exceed 150% of prior longest trail session when introducing MTB.',NULL,'0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (XC Mountain Biking)','D-008','Mountain Biking','Primary',37.0,42.0,42.0,50.0,42.0,55.0,35.0,45.0,'XCO (Olympic): near-VO2max racing, power bursts through technical sections. XCS (Short Track): most intensity-dominated, resembles criterium prep. XCM (Marathon): 3–7 hrs, closer to endurance road cycling — sustained power + technical handling under fatigue. MINIMAL in base (road foundation first). Build/Peak: escalate trail commitment progressively. FULL SUSPENSION 29" now standard at elite — train on race bike setup.','included','XCO (Olympic): near-VO2max racing, power bursts through technical sections.','XCS (Short Track): most intensity-dominated, resembles criterium prep. | XCM (Marathon): 3–7 hrs, closer to endurance road cycling — sustained power + technical handling under fatigue. | MINIMAL in base (road foundation first). | Build/Peak: escalate trail commitment progressively. | FULL SUSPENSION 29" now standard at elite — train on race bike setup.','XCO (Olympic): near-VO2max racing, power bursts through technical sections. XCS (Short Track): most intensity-dominated, resembles criterium prep. XCM (Marathon): 3–7 hrs, closer to endurance road cycling — sustained power + technical handling under fatigue. MINIMAL in base (road foundation first). Build/Peak: escalate trail commitment progressively. FULL SUSPENSION 29" now standard at elite — train on race bike setup.',NULL,'0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (XC Mountain Biking)',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory',6.0,12.0,4.0,8.0,2.0,6.0,2.0,3.0,'Core + hip flexor + single-leg power (road base focus in base phase). ADD: upper body arm endurance and bracing (MTB requires sustained upper body load on technical trails — distinct from road). Explosive leg power for power bursts and technical climbs (XCO/XCS format). SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','included','Core + hip flexor + single-leg power (road base focus in base phase).','ADD: upper body arm endurance and bracing (MTB requires sustained upper body load on technical trails — distinct from road). | Explosive leg power for power bursts and technical climbs (XCO/XCS format). | SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','Core + hip flexor + single-leg power (road base focus in base phase). ADD: upper body arm endurance and bracing (MTB requires sustained upper body load on technical trails — distinct from road). Explosive leg power for power bursts and technical climbs (XCO/XCS format). SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','strength','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (XC Mountain Biking)',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,2.0,5.0,5.0,8.0,'Thoracic spine + lat foam roll (after every MTB session — non-negotiable for upper body recovery). Hip flexor stretch. Shoulder cross-body stretch (MTB upper body stabilization load). Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool after technical sessions.','included','Thoracic spine + lat foam roll (after every MTB session — non-negotiable for upper body recovery).','Hip flexor stretch. | Shoulder cross-body stretch (MTB upper body stabilization load). | Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool after technical sessions.','Thoracic spine + lat foam roll (after every MTB session — non-negotiable for upper body recovery). Hip flexor stretch. Shoulder cross-body stretch (MTB upper body stabilization load). Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool after technical sessions.','mobility','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (XC Mountain Biking)',NULL,'WEEKLY TOTAL TARGET','-',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs  XCO/XCS: intensity emphasis — fewer hours but higher quality. XCM: volume emphasis — back-to-back long rides in peak (same structure as endurance road). NOTE: XC MTB Peak band (82–109%) is wider than single-discipline target but follows Marathon (Mountain) precedent — justified by dual-discipline complexity.','included','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs','XCO/XCS: intensity emphasis — fewer hours but higher quality. | XCM: volume emphasis — back-to-back long rides in peak (same structure as endurance road). | NOTE: XC MTB Peak band (82–109%) is wider than single-discipline target but follows Marathon (Mountain) precedent — justified by dual-discipline complexity.','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs

XCO/XCS: intensity emphasis — fewer hours but higher quality. XCM: volume emphasis — back-to-back long rides in peak (same structure as endurance road). NOTE: XC MTB Peak band (82–109%) is wider than single-discipline target but follows Marathon (Mountain) precedent — justified by dual-discipline complexity.','weekly_total','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Enduro)','D-006','Road Cycling','Primary',57.0,62.0,45.0,53.0,42.0,50.0,52.0,60.0,'AEROBIC BASE = TRANSFER FITNESS: Fresh stages = undertrained base = tired starts = poor times. Road base is mandatory even for descent-focused Enduro athletes. Base = strong aerobic foundation for stage transfers (untimed climbs between stages). Build/Peak = maintain road while introducing descent training. Taper = back to road for multi-day event freshness. Road ≥42% in all phases.','included','AEROBIC BASE = TRANSFER FITNESS: Fresh stages = undertrained base = tired starts = poor times.','Road base is mandatory even for descent-focused Enduro athletes. | Base = strong aerobic foundation for stage transfers (untimed climbs between stages). | Build/Peak = maintain road while introducing descent training. | Taper = back to road for multi-day event freshness. | Road ≥42% in all phases.','AEROBIC BASE = TRANSFER FITNESS: Fresh stages = undertrained base = tired starts = poor times. Road base is mandatory even for descent-focused Enduro athletes. Base = strong aerobic foundation for stage transfers (untimed climbs between stages). Build/Peak = maintain road while introducing descent training. Taper = back to road for multi-day event freshness. Road ≥42% in all phases.',NULL,'0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Enduro)','D-008','Mountain Biking','Primary',32.0,36.0,38.0,45.0,42.0,50.0,32.0,40.0,'DESCENTS = RACE-COMMITMENT INTENSITY, schedule when FRESH (fatigue + high commitment = crash risk). Base = minimal descent training (road foundation first). Build/Peak = escalate descent commitment (2–3 dedicated sessions/week in peak). PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Train in race protection ALWAYS — helmet, knee pads, back protector. MULTI-DAY TAPER: Reduce high-commitment descents 14 days before multi-day event (vs. 7 days for single-day) — CNS-intensive; needs longer recovery window.','included','DESCENTS = RACE-COMMITMENT INTENSITY, schedule when FRESH (fatigue + high commitment = crash risk).','Base = minimal descent training (road foundation first). | Build/Peak = escalate descent commitment (2–3 dedicated sessions/week in peak). | PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Train in race protection ALWAYS — helmet, knee pads, back protector. | MULTI-DAY TAPER: Reduce high-commitment descents 14 days before multi-day event (vs. | 7 days for single-day) — CNS-intensive; | needs longer recovery window.','DESCENTS = RACE-COMMITMENT INTENSITY, schedule when FRESH (fatigue + high commitment = crash risk). Base = minimal descent training (road foundation first). Build/Peak = escalate descent commitment (2–3 dedicated sessions/week in peak). PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Train in race protection ALWAYS — helmet, knee pads, back protector. MULTI-DAY TAPER: Reduce high-commitment descents 14 days before multi-day event (vs. 7 days for single-day) — CNS-intensive; needs longer recovery window.',NULL,'0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Enduro)',NULL,'Strength Training','Accessory',6.0,10.0,4.0,8.0,2.0,6.0,2.0,3.0,'Core + hip flexor + single-leg power + upper body bracing (descent requires sustained upper body load — more than any other cycling format). ADD ECCENTRIC QUAD: Eccentric squats, step-downs, slowing drills — descent stages produce high eccentric quad load; prepare specifically. TRAIN IN PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Knee pads + back protector always during strength. SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','included','Core + hip flexor + single-leg power + upper body bracing (descent requires sustained upper body load — more than any ot','ADD ECCENTRIC QUAD: Eccentric squats, step-downs, slowing drills — descent stages produce high eccentric quad load; | prepare specifically. | TRAIN IN PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Knee pads + back protector always during strength. | SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','Core + hip flexor + single-leg power + upper body bracing (descent requires sustained upper body load — more than any other cycling format). ADD ECCENTRIC QUAD: Eccentric squats, step-downs, slowing drills — descent stages produce high eccentric quad load; prepare specifically. TRAIN IN PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENT: Knee pads + back protector always during strength. SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 2–3 | Build 2 | Peak 1–2 | Taper 1.','strength','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Enduro)',NULL,'Mobility / Recovery','Foundation',3.0,5.0,3.0,5.0,2.0,5.0,5.0,8.0,'Thoracic spine foam roll (after every MTB session). Quad/knee CWI (11–15°C, 10–15 min) after high-commitment descent sessions. Hip flexor stretch. MULTI-DAY RECOVERY: Same-day recovery between Enduro stages — eat, stretch hip flexors and quads, elevation, hydrate before the next stage. Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool.','included','Thoracic spine foam roll (after every MTB session).','Quad/knee CWI (11–15°C, 10–15 min) after high-commitment descent sessions. | Hip flexor stretch. | MULTI-DAY RECOVERY: Same-day recovery between Enduro stages — eat, stretch hip flexors and quads, elevation, hydrate before the next stage. | Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool.','Thoracic spine foam roll (after every MTB session). Quad/knee CWI (11–15°C, 10–15 min) after high-commitment descent sessions. Hip flexor stretch. MULTI-DAY RECOVERY: Same-day recovery between Enduro stages — eat, stretch hip flexors and quads, elevation, hydrate before the next stage. Sleep is the primary CNS recovery tool.','mobility','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
  ('Long Distance / Endurance Cycling (Enduro)',NULL,'WEEKLY TOTAL TARGET','-',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs  Multi-day Enduro events (2–3 days common) require consecutive high-effort days — train back-to-back in peak phase. CRASH RISK: Enduro has the highest crash/impact injury rate of all cycling disciplines. Protective equipment is mandatory in all training descents — never train descents without full protection. All-or-nothing descent commitment: a conservative descent that avoids crashes beats a fast descent with a crash by a large margin.','included','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs','Multi-day Enduro events (2–3 days common) require consecutive high-effort days — train back-to-back in peak phase. | CRASH RISK: Enduro has the highest crash/impact injury rate of all cycling disciplines. | Protective equipment is mandatory in all training descents — never train descents without full protection. | All-or-nothing descent commitment: a conservative descent that avoids crashes beats a fast descent with a crash by a large margin.','WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs

