  ('Cross-Country / Nordic Skiing','D-028','Cross-Country Skiing','Primary',70.0,80.0,75.0,85.0,80.0,90.0,80.0,90.0,'WORLD-CLASS: 88.7% LIT / 6.4% MIT / 4.8% HIT (pyramidal). Recreational: similar ratios at lower volume. SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 5-6 | Build 5-6 | Peak 5-7 | Taper 4-5. Long session (3-5 hrs): 1-2x/week all phases. Intensity sessions: every 3-4 days, never back-to-back.  OFF-SNOW SPLIT (Base only — when no snow available): 50–60% roller skiing, 20–30% run/cycle. Roller ski is the primary specificity tool when snow is absent.','included','WORLD-CLASS: 88.7% LIT / 6.4% MIT / 4.8% HIT (pyramidal).','Recreational: similar ratios at lower volume. | SESSIONS/WEEK: Base 5-6 | Build 5-6 | Peak 5-7 | Taper 4-5. | Long session (3-5 hrs): 1-2x/week all phases. | Intensity sessions: every 3-4 days, never back-to-back. | OFF-SNOW SPLIT (Base only — when no snow available): 50–60% roller skiing, 20–30% run/cycle. | Roller ski is the primary specificity tool when snow is absent.','WORLD-CLASS: 88.7% LIT / 6.4% MIT / 4.8% HIT (pyramidal). Recreational: similar ratios at lower volume.
