  ('Triathlon (Sprint)','Base',6.0,9.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 6–9 hrs | BUILD: 7–11 hrs | PEAK: 8–12 hrs | TAPER: 5–7 hrs

Sprint athletes can race well at 8–10 hrs/week peak. Intensity quality matters more than volume at this format. 80/20 INTENSITY: 80% genuinely easy (conversational). The most common error is training too much at moderate intensity — hard enough to impair recovery, not hard enough to drive adaptation. Draft-legal Sprint racing requires tactical group skills — include 1 group ride/week if targeting ITU format.','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
