  ('Triathlon (Standard / Olympic)','Base',8.0,12.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs | BUILD: 10–14 hrs | PEAK: 12–15 hrs | TAPER: 7–9 hrs

Mixed Relay athletes: each athlete trains only their assigned discipline at full depth. Relay swimmer does not train cycling or running. Handoff transition zone mechanics are a distinct trainable skill (separate from individual T1/T2). 80/20 INTENSITY: Grey-zone (moderate) training is the most common intensity error — hard enough to impair recovery, not hard enough to drive VO2max adaptation.','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
