  ('Triathlon (Full / Ironman 140.6)','Base',14.0,18.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 14–18 hrs | BUILD: 18–22 hrs | PEAK: 20–25 hrs | TAPER: 8–10 hrs

Full IM is the highest-volume triathlon format. Consistency over 20–24 weeks is the primary predictor of race-day readiness — 1 perfect 25-hr week surrounded by 10-hr weeks does not prepare you for 8–17 hrs of racing. 80/20 INTENSITY: Non-negotiable at this volume — grey-zone training produces burnout, injury, and underperformance. SLEEP: Primary recovery tool. 8+ hrs/night mandatory in peak training phase — sleep deprivation at high IM training volume accelerates overtraining syndrome. TAPER: Aggressive volume cut (40–50%) 3 weeks out; maintain 2 intensity sessions/week until race week. No changes to bike fit, shoe setup, or nutrition strategy in final 3 weeks.','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
