  ('Skimo (Individual / Team)','Base',8.0,12.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs (dry-land) | BUILD: 9–14 hrs | PEAK: 10–16 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs

Individual format is the standard skimo training reference. TEAM: Add partner coordination sessions (proximity drills, pace-matching) from Build phase. Team racing requires race-partner chemistry — train together, not just individually. SEASONAL STRUCTURE (unique to all skimo): Off-snow (May–Oct): running and hiking primary. Pre-season on-snow (Nov–Dec): technique and gentle volume. Competition season (Jan–Mar): race-simulation and taper. 80/20 applies to skinning — 80% Zone 2 aerobic, 20% threshold.','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
