  ('Skimo (Long Distance / Grand Traverse)','Base',8.0,12.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS: BASE: 8–12 hrs (dry-land) | BUILD: 10–16 hrs | PEAK: 12–20 hrs | TAPER: 5–8 hrs

Back-to-back long days are counted in PEAK total and will be the highest-load training unit — plan the entire week around them. NIGHT SESSION: Include 1 overnight skinning session in peak for events with night segments (Grand Traverse). OFF-SNOW BASE: Ultra-style back-to-back long hikes/runs with poles are the most specific substitute. TAPER: 2–3 weeks. Reduce back-to-back days in final 2 weeks. Final high-commitment descent: 14 days before race (longer CNS taper vs. single-day).','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
