  ('Fell Running','Base',6.0,10.0,'WEEKLY TARGET HOURS:
BASE: 6-10 hrs
BUILD: 8-14 hrs
PEAK: 10-16 hrs
TAPER: 5-8 hrs

Category A (strenuous) races and longer fell races (L): upper end of range.
Category B/C short (S) and medium (M): lower end.
Mountain Marathons: 2-day events require a peak week of 14-18 hrs in the 4-6 weeks preceding.

Bob Graham Round / Ramsey Round preparation: specialist plans of 16-22 hrs peak over 6-month dedicated training block.

VERTICAL GAIN is co-equal metric with hours, same as mountain running (D-024).

MANDATORY KIT FAMILIARITY: Ongoing throughout training. Athletes must remain familiar with mandatory race kit (waterproofs, whistle, map, compass, food, hat/gloves) at all times. Full pre-race kit check 1–2 weeks pre-race. Not a separate training discipline — handled via integration in long runs and recce sessions.','hrs','0A-v1.6.6','2026-06-10T17:40:05.453426+00:00'::timestamptz),
